@node "Intro" "Multi Read Introduction"
                               ***What is it?***

      This is a simple little rexx script I wrote to replace the standard
      RF command, which I wrote becuase i was tired of having to type in
      the complete path/filename to each file when browsing through 
      multiple ANSI files.
                               The Features are:

       1:  Uses a file requestor to select files. (On local ports only.)
       2:  Allows Selection of multiple files.(On local ports only.)
       3:  Supports same usage as the original RF command.
@endnode

@node "usage" "How to use it!"
                                  ***Usage***


       When used in Local mode:    
           1:  You can type "RF <filename>" and it will work exactly
               the same as the standard RF command.
           2:  If you only type in "RF" you will be presented with a file
               reqestor.  You can select as many files to view as you
               wish.

       When used from a remote terminal:
           1:  It wil function almost exactly the same as the standard 
               RF command.  You can enter "RF <filename>", or if you
               only enter "RF" you will be presented with a prompt for
               a file name
@endnode

@node "req" "Requirments"

                               ***REQUIRMENTS***

                      Cnet V3.x (not yet tested with 4.x)
             Reqtools.library,  Version  38.1436**  (NOT INCLUDED)
            rexxreqtools.library,  Version  37.95**  (NOT INCLUDED)

         **  May Work with earlier versions of these libs.  These are 
             the versions I am using.  The Latest version of reqtools
             are available on aminet in util/libs/ReqToolsUsr.lha
@endnode

